history.content: The CS conflict form does not require you to be on the waitlist. (It did initially but that was a mistake exactly because of situations like you describe).

children.subject:
Does that mean I actually can't save a spot on the waitlist?

So in order to enroll, would I have to wait until there is both open space in the class and no one on the waitlist, since I can't jump the waitlist?

The forms don't get processed until Phase 2 anyway.

But if they were processed in Phase 1, then your form would not be processed, since the department can't enroll you into the course.
I filled the form, but I have taken 13 units as safety. What happens now?

history.content:
I am enrolled in a class that has a time conflict with 61B. I know that if you're on the waitlist for 61B you can use the CS Time Conflict Form. But since 61B is still technically open with the remaining seats marked as reserved (I am not EECS/COE), I can't even enroll onto the waitlist. Instead, since it's open I'm prompted to fill out the CalCentral Time Conflict Form, which will fail because there are actually no available seats.

Given this, is there any way to get on the 61B waitlist? Unless the CalCentral form will put me on the waitlist, I don't see how else I can get on without having to drop the currently enrolled class.
history.subject: Can't enroll in 61B waitlist?
